properties.name: Marshall
properties.desc: Orange overhang with bolts south of the cove. large ledge and slab at the bottom. lots of plants at the top out.

properties.name: Baldwin
properties.desc: Low water grey wall with small roof just north of the cove. bullet headwall.

properties.name: Thurman
properties.desc: Yellowish wall on the south side of the cove is a little chossy but climbable. north side of the cove has two or thee good climbs with bolts. a little further north there is a small boulder for warming up.

properties.name: North Maugham
properties.desc: White wall north of the cove with a dark grey bullet head wall. there's a pile of rocks under the left side of the cave and one to the right of the wall.

properties.name: Davis Cove (South)
properties.desc: Overhung climb and a traverse. We climbed at 682, not sure what the min is.
properties.approach: Kayak from the boat ramp or park near the campsite above and walk towards the cove.

properties.name: Thrasher
properties.desc: Bullet hard orange overhang inside the cove on the north side.

properties.name: Gracy
properties.desc: Dark grey, orange, and brown godstone wall north of the cove half way to davis cove. large slab at the base of the cliff.

properties.name: Maugham
properties.desc: big jug covered grotto inside the cove on the south side with a large ledge under it

properties.name: Greykull
properties.desc: White tufa covered walls on the lago vista side of the lake. top out into a lot of plantlife. weird ecosystem

properties.name: Giles
properties.desc: Large white virt dihedral leading to big multi-tiered roof.

properties.name: Briarcliff
properties.desc: Giant bullet grey tufa and stalactite covered scoop at the back of the cove near the briarcliff marina
